      • getStoredObject

        public StoredObject getStoredObject(FileObject fileObject,
                           java.lang.String filename)
        Get the URL corresponding to a stored object. This method is used to find the URL of a stored object corresponding to a queued object.
        Parameters:
        fileObject - the object.
        filename - the name by which the object is stored in the FileStorage Service. This name may be different from the name contained in the File of the FileObject because the supplied FileObject may be a copy of the object which was queued under another name.
        Returns:
        the URL corresponding to the stored object, or null if no object corresponding to the supplied object is stored.

      • store

        public FileObject store(FileObject fileObject)
        Store an object if the object is of a type that the StorageService is configured to accept. If the StorageService is not configured to accept the object type, return the original object; otherwise, return either the passed object or the stored object depending on whether the returnStoredFile attribute was "no" or "yes". If the storage attempt fails, quarantine the input object if a quarantine was defined in the configuration, and return null to stop further processing.
        Specified by:
        store in interface StorageService
        Parameters:
        fileObject - the object to process.
        Returns:
        either the original FileObject or the stored FileObject, or null if the object could not be stored.
